   KNOWLEDGE MANAGEMENT, CIKM 2021},
Year = {2021},
Pages = {68-77},
Abstract = {We present Gradient Activation Maps (GAM) - a machinery for explaining
   predictions made by visual similarity and classification models. By
   gleaning localized gradient and activation information from multiple
   network layers, GAM offers improved visual explanations, when compared
   to existing alternatives. The algorithmic advantages of GAM are
   explained in detail, and validated empirically, where it is shown that
   GAM outperforms its alternatives across various tasks and datasets.},
